## GitHub integration
- **Live in:** `.claude/memory/decisions.md` — "GitHub integration" line
- **Current:** {{GITHUB_INTEGRATION}}
- **Options:** `yes` (issues, labels, PRs) · `no` (fully local — skills skip all `gh` calls)

## ci-on-claude
- **Live in:** read by `/commit` (append `[skip ci]` when off) — record here; no repo variable needed
- **Current:** {{CI_ON_CLAUDE}}  (default `no` for apps, `yes` recommended for cross-platform libraries)
- **Options:** `no` — Claude's commits carry `[skip ci]`, so GitHub Actions runs only on human commits + releases (0 Actions minutes for Claude's work) · `yes` — CI also runs on Claude's commits (matrix/multi-env local can't reproduce)

## release-runner
- **Live in:** `/release` skill
- **Current:** {{RELEASE_RUNNER}}  (default `local`)
- **Options:** `local` — Claude runs `scripts/release.sh` in-session (no Actions minutes) · `ci` — trigger the GitHub release workflow instead (keeps publish secrets out of the session)

## Pause threshold (unsupervised)
- **Live in:** `.claude/memory/settings.md` (runtime; set via `/unsupervised on [threshold]`)
- **Current:** 90 (default) where usage is readable (local/VS Code); no guard in cloud or in supervised mode — runs into the limit, and `/auto-resume` (if on) recovers
- **Options:** integer 10–99

## Auto-resume (recover after a limit)
- **Live in:** `.claude/memory/settings.md` (runtime; set via `/auto-resume on|off`) — **independent of unsupervised**
- **Current:** off by default; when on, an interrupted run wakes itself after the limit resets and continues (cloud: recovery heartbeat; local: SessionStart/`claude-loop.sh`)
- **Options:** `on` · `off`
